The Alcaic is so called from the Greek poet Alcaeus of Lesbos, who is said to have invented it. It is employed by Horace more frequently than any other metre, and is especially used when a lofty and dignified tone is assumed, being there- fore selected for Odes 4, 14 and 15 which are of a strictly formal character. The ninth Ode is also in this metre.
